  m_Name: Parlor Relic
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::CodexEntry
  title: Cigar Box
  description: "Tobacco boxes were small containers used to store and carry pipe
    tobacco, which was commonly used among upper-class men in the 18th and 19th centuries.
    They were often made from wood, metal, or decorated materials and could be highly
    ornate, reflecting the owner\u2019s wealth and taste. Tobacco was typically enjoyed
    socially in rooms like parlors, where smoking was part of conversation and leisure."
